did.head: Collection Overview
did.abstract: This collection is in fifteen boxes and contains black and white photographs, photo albums, correspondence, letters, scrapbooks, class notes, student papers and drawings, writings, publications, newspaper clippings, record books and memorabilia from the commencement and reunions of the Class of 1894.

bioghist.p: The Class of 1894 was the sixteenth entering class and the sixteenth graduating class of Smith College.

scopecontent.p: The Class Years 1894 records, 1823-1977, contain materials describing the history of the Class of 1894. Types of materials include black and white photographs, photo albums, correspondence, letters, scrapbooks, class notes, student papers and drawings, writings, publications, newspaper clippings, record books and memorabilia from the commencement and reunions of the Class of 1894.

accessrestrict.p: The records are open for research according to the regulations of the Smith College Archives without any additional restrictions.

userestrict.p: Single photocopies may be made for research purposes. Permission to publish material from the documents must be requested from the Smith College Archives. Smith College owns copyright to any published material relating to college events and activities. Provenance and copyright ownership of other materials is unknown and researchers are responsible for determining any question of copyright.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please use the following format when citing materials from this collection:
Class of 1894 Records, Box #, Smith College Archives.

acqinfo.p: The Class of 1894 Records were created by the students and donated to the College Archives.
